a60 21

    <p>
    LibreSSL portable releases are signed with a
    <a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=signify&sektion=1">signify(1)</a>
    public key:
    <a href="https://github.com/libressl-portable/portable/commit/c5c2aa37be6134f6552070ab21f49d53ebfe86e6">RWQg/nutTVqCUVUw8OhyHt9n51IC8mdQRd1b93dOyVrwtIXmMI+dtGFe</a>
    <h4>Release Signing</h4>
    <p>
    Releases can be verified from within the OpenBSD operating system or
    by using an unofficial
    <a href="http://www.linuxquestions.org/questions/slackware-14/openbsd%27s-new-john-hancock-4175504101/">Linux port of the 'signify' utility.</a>

    <h4>Mailing Lists</h4>
    <p>
    There are two mailing lists for Libressl:
    <p>
    <a href="email:libressl@@openbsd.org">libressl@@openbsd.org</a> - public list for technical discussion about LibreSSL on any operating system.
    <p>
    <a href="email:libressl-security@@openbsd.org">libressl-security@@openbsd.org</a> - private list for reporting severe vulnerabilities in OpenSSL or LibreSSL to the core LibreSSL team.
    <p>
    See <a href="http://www.openbsd.org/mail.html">http://www.openbsd.org/mail.html</a> for more details on posting or subscribing.
