<body>
<section class="libre-ssl">
<hgroup>
<header>
<center><img src="ChePuff.jpg"></center>
<h1>LibreSSL</h1>
</header>
</hgroup>
<section class="introduction">
<p>LibreSSL is a <strong>FREE</strong> version of the SSL/TLS protocol
forked from <a
href="http://wiki.openssl.org/index.php/Code_Quality">OpenSSL</a></p>
<p>
At the moment we are <a
href="http://freshbsd.org/search?project=openbsd&q=file.name:libssl">too
busy deleting and rewriting code</a> to make a decent web page. No we
don't want help making web pages, thank you.
</p>
<p>Check back here soon for updates.</p>
</section>
<section class="resources">
<hgroup>
<header>
<h2>Resources:</h2>
</header>
</hgroup>
<section class="open-bsd">
<hgroup>
<header>
<h3>For OpenBSD</h3>
</header>
</hgroup>
<ul class="indent-list">
<li><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/ftp.html#http">FTP</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/anoncvs.html">AnonCVS</a></li>
<li><a href="http://cvsweb.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/src/lib/libssl">CVSWeb</a></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section>
<hgroup>
<header>
<h3>For other OS's</h3>
</header>
</hgroup>
<p>
<ul class="indent-list">
<li><strong>LibreSSL Portable</strong> can be found in the LibreSSL directory of <A HREF=http://www.openbsd.org/ftp.html>OpenBSD mirror sites</A> (the master is at <A HREF="http://ftp.openbsd.org/pub/OpenBSD/LibreSSL">http://ftp.openbsd.org/pub/OpenBSD/LibreSSL</A>)</li>
<BR>
LibreSSL portable releases are signed with the <A HREF="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=signify&sektion=1">signify(1)</A> public key <A HREF="https://github.com/libressl-portable/portable/commit/c5c2aa37be6134f6552070ab21f49d53ebfe86e6">RWQg/nutTVqCUVUw8OhyHt9n51IC8mdQRd1b93dOyVrwtIXmMI+dtGFe</A>
<P>
<li><strong>Caution</strong> - LibreSSL depends on certain intrinsic
functions for security. If your OS provides these functions (e.g.
arc4random, calloc, issetugid, getentropy etc.), LibreSSL will assume
the provided implementation is robust and use it.  It is beyond the
scope of the LibreSSL project to validate third party implementations.
Issues with OS provided intrinsic functions need to be addressed by
the target OS.</li>
<P>
<li>We have a github repository clone as <A href="https://github.com/libressl-portable/">libressl-portable</A> on github for the curious. This is a copy of the working respositories which are not maintained on github.</li>
<P>
<li><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/papers/bsdcan14-libressl">LibreSSL Presentation by Bob Beck from BSDCAN 2014</a></li>
</p>
<P>
<li> Please note, we still need a <a
href="http://www.openbsdfoundation.org/">Stable Commitment of
Funding</a> to support an increased development and porting
effort. </li>
</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section class="acknowledgements">
<p>
LibreSSL is primarily developed by <a
href="http://www.openbsd.org/">the OpenBSD Project</a>, and its first
inclusion into an operating system will be in <a
href="http://www.openbsd.org/56.html">OpenBSD 5.6</a>.
</p>
<p>
LibreSSL is supported financially by <a
href="http://www.openbsdfoundation.org/">The OpenBSD Foundation</a> as
well as by the <a href="http://www.openbsd.org/donations.html">The
OpenBSD Project</a>. Please consider <a
href="http://www.openbsdfoundation.org/donations.html">donating</a> to
support our efforts.<br>
</p>
</section>
<section class="we-love-web-devs-especially-those-that-write-blink-tags-for-us">
<p>This page scientifically designed to annoy web hipsters. <a
href="http://www.openbsdfoundation.org/donations.html">Donate now</a>
to stop the Comic Sans and Blink Tags</p>
</section>
